         <abstract>
            <p>A few studies have been published which investigate profitable decision rules for an investment program of writing Call options for common stock. Much more investigation of Call writing is required before the actual profit potential is clearly understood. This study explores an alternate route to Call writing profits. Here Call options are supported with ownership of convertible bonds. As compared to holding stock, convertible bonds are found to offer a definite increase in rate of return from lower margin requirements. Convertibles also provide some improvement over stock in price protection of a Call Writer on the downside.</p>
          </abstract>
